ZH: 我的脚趾疼得厉害，可能是因为长时间站立的缘故。
EN: My toes hurt a lot, probably because of standing for a long time.

ZH: 她的脚趾上有一个可爱的小指甲。
EN: She has a cute little toenail on her toe.

ZH: 天气太热了，我决定穿凉鞋露出脚趾。
EN: It's too hot, so I decided to wear sandals and show off my toes.

ZH: 我不小心摔倒了，结果摔伤了脚趾。
EN: I accidentally fell and injured my toe.

ZH: 我需要买一双合适大小的袜子，以免勒到脚趾。
EN: I need to buy a pair of socks that are the right size to avoid squeezing my toes.

ZH: 他每天晚上都会给自己的脚趾按摩，以放松脚部肌肉。
EN: He massages his toes every night to relax the muscles in his feet.

ZH: 这双鞋子太紧了，会挤疼我的脚趾。
EN: These shoes are too tight and squeeze my toes.

ZH: 我喜欢在沙滩上感觉细软的沙子蹭着我的脚趾。
EN: I like the feeling of soft sand rubbing against my toes on the beach.

ZH: 我的脚趾甲上涂了亮橙色的指甲油。
EN: I painted my toenails with bright orange nail polish.

ZH: 每天晚上睡觉前，我都会轻轻地拔拉我的脚趾，以放松肌肉。
EN: Every night before going to bed, I gently stretch my toes to relax the muscles.

ZH: 捡起这个小石子时，我不小心磕伤了脚趾。
EN: I accidentally bumped my toe when picking up this small stone.

ZH: 听说脚趾间健康的空隙可以帮助预防真菌感染。
EN: I heard that having healthy gaps between the toes can help prevent fungal infections.

ZH: 为了保持脚趾的干爽，我会在夏天多穿透气的鞋子。
EN: To keep my toes dry, I will wear more breathable shoes in the summer.

ZH: 她的脚趾十分柔软，能够轻松伸展。
EN: Her toes are very flexible and can easily stretch.

ZH: 我在沙滩上玩耍时，不小心碰到了一块锋利的贝壳，划伤了脚趾。
EN: When playing on the beach, I accidentally touched a sharp seashell and cut my toe.

ZH: 他用锤子砸到脚趾了，痛得他直咬牙。
EN: He accidentally hit his toe with a hammer, causing him great pain.

ZH: 每天晚上，我会仔细检查脚趾是否有任何异常。
EN: Every night, I carefully check if there are any abnormalities on my toes.

ZH: 运动时，我需要确保脚趾与鞋子的前端有足够的空间。
EN: When exercising, I need to make sure there is enough space for my toes at the front of the shoe.

ZH: 脚趾疼痛可能是因为穿的鞋子太小了。
EN: Toe pain may be caused by wearing shoes that are too small.

ZH: 我在海滩上沙滩排球时，不小心扭伤了脚趾。
EN: I accidentally sprained my toe while playing beach volleyball.

